    <title>Scaling Laws for Multilingual Language Models</title>
    <summary>  We study scaling laws for multilingual language models trained on
diverse corpora spanning 50 languages. Our findings suggest that
cross-lingual transfer improves sub-linearly with model size.
</summary>
